falco
------------------------------------------
C++ implementation of FastQC for quality control of sequencing data

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libhts3-1.23.1-1bl1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  zlib0-1.3.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libhts-devel-1.23.1-1bl1
  make-4.4.1-2
  zlib-devel-1.3.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/smithlabcode/falco

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/smithlabcode/falco/archive/refs/tags/v1.3.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack falco-1.3.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./falco-1.3.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/falco-1.3.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/falco-1.3.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(falco)
  /usr/bin/falco.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/falco.README
  /usr/share/doc/falco/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/falco/README.md

